p.q:
That, at the sitting on Tuesday 26th October, notwithstanding the provisions of Standing Orders No. 14 (Exempted business) and No. 15 (Prayers against statutory instruments, &c. (negative procedure), the Speaker shall put the Questions necessary to dispose of proceedings on:


(a) the Motion in the name of Mr. John Smith relating to Health and Safety at Mines not later than Seven o'clock;

(b) the Motion in the name of Secretary Sir Patrick Mayhew relating to Northern Ireland (Education and Libraries) not later than one and a half hours after their commencement; and

(c) the Motion in the name of Mr. John Smith relating to Education (School Teachers' Pay and Conditions) not later than one and a half hours after their commencement;

and the third Motion may be proceeded with after the expiry of the time for opposed business.—[Mr. Michael Brown.]
